# Vectorless RAG

- Use when exact matching, structured metadata, or full-text search suffices over semantic similarity.
- Leverage BM25/Elasticsearch/OpenSearch for keyword + fuzzy retrieval.
- SQL-based retrieval: pre-filter with WHERE clauses, then rank with full-text indexes.
- Graph traversal for relationship-based context without vector embeddings.
- LLM-generated query expansion: rewrite user query into search terms, not embedding lookup.
- PageIndex / hierarchical document trees: navigate structure instead of chunk similarity.
- Cheaper and faster for domains with precise terminology (legal, medical codes, SKUs).
- Combine with small vector index only for ambiguous natural language queries.
- Evaluate whether vector search adds value before adding embedding infrastructure.
- Cache parsed document indexes; rebuilding indexes is often the bottleneck, not search.
